    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average)\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-13}{6} \\approx -2.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (3.1667)^2 \\approx 10.037 \\\\\n(12 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (14.1667)^2 \\approx 200.666 \\\\\n(-17 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (-14.8333)^2 \\approx 219.999 \\\\\n(-3 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (-0.8333)^2 \\approx 0.694 \\\\\n(-11 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (-8.8333)^2 \\approx 78.000 \\\\\n(-5 - (-2.1667))^2 &= (-2.8333)^2 \\approx 8.027 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n10.037 + 200.666 + 219.999 + 0.694 + 78.000 + 8.027 \\approx 517.326\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $ n - 1 $ (sample variance)\n\n$$\n\\text{Sample Variance} = \\frac{517.326}{6 - 1} = \\frac{517.326}{5} \\approx 103.465\n$$\n\n---\n\n###"
